title: Ooltewah High School player Named Player Of The Week
text:
Thursday, October 1 2015, 03:12 PM EDT Ooltewah High School player Named Player Of The Week An Ooltewah High School player got a spotlight that she didn’t see coming.Tuesday night at Ooltewah High School, the volleyball team held a breast cancer fund raiser for the Mary Ellen Locher Foundation. During the evening, senior Alex Biro got a surprise. She was recognized for her outstanding play.The American Volleyball Coaches Association named her the Player of the Week for all of Tennessee. Max Preps also applauded her performance.That was for her outstanding play during the week of September 7th.In eight games, she had 58 kills, 11 digs, two aces and eight blocks. Congratulations Alex Biro. Ooltewah High School player Named Player Of The Week Related Stories Check Back Often for NewsChannel9 Sponsored Events!
